headline.main: Latest Intelligence by the Atlantic.; BY TELEGRAPH FROM SANDY HOOK.

docs.lead_paragraph: The Cunard steamer Asia arrived out at Liverpool at 2 o'clock, P. M., on the 20th Feb. The screw steamer City of Glasgow, from Philadelphia, also arrived out on the 20th. The terrific gale at Liverpool, reported by the Alps, had entailed no casualties on American shipping, excepting some of trivial importance.

docs.lead_paragraph: The CUNARD Screw-Steamer Alps, with the European mails of the 18th ult., arrived at this port at about 9 o'clock this forenoon. The Alps brings twenty-nine passengers, and the mails of the 18th for the United States and Canada. On the 19th, the Alps passed the ship A. Z., round to Liverpool from New-York.

headline.main: THIRTY-THIRD CONGRESS.........First Session.; SENATE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES.

docs.lead_paragraph: MR. EVERETT WISHES TO RECORD HIS VOTE AGAINST THE NEBRASKA BILL. Mr. EVERETT said that he was absent on Saturday morning, when the final vote was taken on the Nebraska bill. He was severely indisposed at that time, and, as was well known, his health had not been good for some time. He was on that night over-fatigued, and was unable to remain till the hour when the vote was taken.

Cleaning the Streets--Vigorous Measures taken at Law.

docs.lead_paragraph: Our City authorities have set themselves vigorously at work to clean the streets from the dirt and filth which have accumulated since the cowardly resignation of ARCULARIUS, and the refusal of the contractors to fulfil their stipulations.
